It's not lighting up!

12:28.165 --> 12:30.098
Oh, boy.

12:30.100 --> 12:32.234
He'll pay for that at commercial time.

12:32.236 --> 12:33.769
What happens at commercial?

12:33.771 --> 12:37.172
<i>And we're clear to commercial.</i>

12:38.143 --> 12:40.376
No! Please don't! Don't eat me!

12:40.378 --> 12:41.710
Yuh-oh.
- No!

12:41.712 --> 12:44.513
- No-o-o-o!!
- Oh, boy.

12:44.515 --> 12:45.643
Sounds bad.

12:46.050 --> 12:48.784
<i>We're on in 3, 2...</i>

12:51.321 --> 12:53.389
Oh, God. He's gone.

12:53.391 --> 12:55.591
It's a good thing I'm
clearly irreplaceable

12:55.593 --> 12:57.026
and integral to the show.

13:06.637 --> 13:10.639
Charlie, now how about
something a little harder?

13:10.641 --> 13:14.710
Here's a rowdy little number called
"Volcano Blast Freakout."

13:18.449 --> 13:20.449
Hot, hot, hot.

13:20.451 --> 13:22.918
Did you hear that guy say,
"Don't eat me"?

13:22.920 --> 13:24.986
That makes me think Alistair ate him.

13:24.988 --> 13:28.323
He doesn't like it when
people mess up his show.

13:28.325 --> 13:30.659
You having a nice time, Stan?

13:31.157 --> 13:33.128
You know my name. That's cool!

13:33.130 --> 13:34.529
Hey, what is this place?

13:34.531 --> 13:37.933
This is a party, baby,
and parties are fun.

13:37.935 --> 13:41.937
So when the camera's on,
you will make nice conversation,

13:41.939 --> 13:43.939
you will keep a drink in hand,

13:43.941 --> 13:46.876
and you will listen to and love

13:46.878 --> 13:50.412
every bit of jazz you hear.

13:50.414 --> 13:52.347
But I like swamp rock.

13:52.349 --> 13:54.283
- No.
- What if we want to leave?

13:54.285 --> 13:55.885
Leave? Why?

13:55.887 --> 13:57.486
You're with other nighthawks,

13:57.488 --> 14:00.722
solo creatures who
enjoy mature pleasures.

14:00.749 --> 14:02.224
Face it, Stan.

14:02.272 --> 14:04.560
- You're a sensualist.
- I know.

14:04.562 --> 14:06.095
But I have a family.

14:06.097 --> 14:07.897
Do you, now?

14:07.899 --> 14:09.030
Yeah, I do.

14:09.032 --> 14:11.767
It's just hard to remember their names.

14:11.769 --> 14:14.836
I told you. I told you.

14:14.838 --> 14:16.838
Francine, Hayley, Steve, Klaus,

14:16.840 --> 14:18.440
Roger. Good, good.

14:18.442 --> 14:20.175
Come on, Tuttle. We can't forget.

14:20.177 --> 14:22.644
I can't remember my family.

14:22.646 --> 14:24.513
- You don't have one.
- Oh.

14:24.515 --> 14:27.449
Don't worry. I still have <i>my</i> family.

14:27.451 --> 14:29.318
- _
- We got to get out of here.

14:29.320 --> 14:31.520
But how? You saw that guy.

14:31.522 --> 14:34.590
We can't call the elevator.

14:34.592 --> 14:36.992
Maybe we don't have to.

14:44.067 --> 14:45.400
- Welcome...
- Pardon. Pardon. Excuse me.

14:45.402 --> 14:47.669
- Excuse me. Excuse me.
- I'm with him.

15:03.287 --> 15:05.454
I think we got away!

15:08.425 --> 15:11.160
- It's all fake!
- Let's try the soup.

15:11.162 --> 15:13.895
That's how you can tell
if it's a real diner.

15:13.897 --> 15:15.497
We're still on the show.

15:15.499 --> 15:18.634
Stan, look! The tree!

15:18.636 --> 15:21.436
Follow the color!

15:21.438 --> 15:22.638
This is the way home!

15:22.640 --> 15:26.375
Langley Falls, here we come!

15:26.377 --> 15:28.177
And maybe there was something appealing

15:28.179 --> 15:29.645
about that bachelor vibe.

15:29.647 --> 15:32.581
Because, boy,
the family was driving me nuts.

15:32.583 --> 15:34.583
You wouldn't know what that's like,
but trust me.

15:34.585 --> 15:37.252
I pretend my fingers are my family...

15:37.254 --> 15:39.254
Mama Thumb always nagging,

15:39.256 --> 15:41.857
Uncle Index with the corny jokes.

15:41.859 --> 15:43.325
What can I say?

15:43.327 --> 15:44.794
They're a handful!

15:45.875 --> 15:47.262
♪ I got Francine ♪

15:47.264 --> 15:48.730
♪ I got Steve ♪

15:48.732 --> 15:50.599
♪ Uh, I got Harley ♪

15:50.601 --> 15:52.934
♪ I got Clark, I want to say Bruce ♪

15:52.936 --> 15:55.937
- Take it, Tuttle!
- ♪ I got no one ♪

15:55.939 --> 15:57.339
Take it, Stan!

16:00.011 --> 16:02.277
Welp, see you around the neighborhood,
Tuttle, old boy.

16:02.279 --> 16:05.481
Yeah. I should get going, too.

16:05.483 --> 16:07.416
Oh, yeah. You have nobody.

16:07.418 --> 16:08.950
Turn off the car, you idiot.

16:08.952 --> 16:11.286
You're coming inside,
you big, fat idiot.

16:11.500 --> 16:12.621
You mean it?

16:12.623 --> 16:14.690
Yeah. You live with me now.

16:14.692 --> 16:16.625
I'll convert the shed
into a room for you.

16:16.627 --> 16:19.761
- I won't insulate it.
- Stan, I have a house.

16:19.763 --> 16:22.097
It's nothing. You'll sleep
on some old car batteries.

16:22.099 --> 16:23.565
I won't hear another word.

16:23.567 --> 16:25.634
Now come watch me hug my family.

16:25.636 --> 16:27.969
Beloved ones, I'm home!

16:30.307 --> 16:32.041
Welcome back, nighthawks.

16:32.043 --> 16:33.909
We've been expecting you.

16:38.782 --> 16:42.251
Oh, no. I'm gonna forget them forever.

17:05.742 --> 17:08.477
Have you heard the new hi-fi's
with the quadraphonic sound?

17:08.479 --> 17:11.413
They're really the best
for listening to jazz.

17:11.415 --> 17:14.616
It sounds like,
"Skeedle-dee-deep-do-bop-do-bop,

17:14.617 --> 17:18.954
scoop-doop, sly-gar,
flarga-marga, smee-boo."

17:18.955 --> 17:21.089
A man can't be himself in the kitchen.

17:21.092 --> 17:23.157
It's not his domain.

17:23.160 --> 17:27.429
But what about when <i>he</i> gets hungry,
and <i>she's</i> not there?

17:27.431 --> 17:30.699
Well, the space-age wet bar of tomorrow

17:30.701 --> 17:32.902
can satisfy his hunger.

17:32.904 --> 17:35.771
A Rumaki-Maker-Matic, folks.

17:35.773 --> 17:38.974
Just plug it in,
load the hopper with chicken liver,

17:38.976 --> 17:42.043
and within minutes,
nuclear-hot hors d'oeuvres

17:42.045 --> 17:43.378
plop out all over

17:43.380 --> 17:46.782
this green tray that
looks like a cabbage.

17:46.784 --> 17:49.318
- Ah!
- Ooh!

17:49.320 --> 17:51.320
Now, picture it. It's 11:15.

17:51.322 --> 17:52.988
You're at the Sands.

17:52.990 --> 17:56.725
Frank Sinatra's overflow girls
are starting to get hungry.

17:56.727 --> 17:59.328
They say they want melted
cheese and lots of it.

17:59.330 --> 18:02.063
Time for fondue.

18:02.065 --> 18:03.198
Fondue.

18:03.200 --> 18:04.866
With an electric fondue set,

18:04.868 --> 18:06.868
it's fast, it's easy and clean,

18:06.870 --> 18:09.004
and lets you eat more cheese

18:09.006 --> 18:11.473
more quickly than ever before.

18:11.475 --> 18:13.408
Fondue! Fondue.

18:13.410 --> 18:14.876
Electric fondue!

18:14.878 --> 18:17.012
Bingo-bango, hot cheese on tap!

18:17.014 --> 18:18.880
My wife! My wife, Fondue!

18:18.882 --> 18:20.682
No, Fondine. <i>Francine!</i>

18:20.684 --> 18:24.720
I remember Francine, and, oh,
how she loved her fondue!

18:24.722 --> 18:25.821
Tuttle! Wake up!

18:26.612 --> 18:27.756
Francine!

18:27.758 --> 18:29.090
Hayley! Steve!

18:29.092 --> 18:31.226
Klaus! Roger!

18:31.228 --> 18:32.894
I'm not a nighthawk!

18:32.896 --> 18:34.830
I want my family!

18:36.900 --> 18:39.034
We're going to take a commercial break,

18:39.036 --> 18:42.371
and when we return,
I promise the party will be...

18:42.373 --> 18:44.439
back on track.

18:44.441 --> 18:45.574
Stan, are you okay?

18:45.576 --> 18:48.177
You're wearing the wall like a hat.

18:48.179 --> 18:49.645
Whoa.

18:52.650 --> 18:54.916
I came in through the static.

18:54.947 --> 18:56.918
This is the way out!

18:59.457 --> 19:01.923
<i>And we're clear to commercial.</i>

19:25.349 --> 19:26.682
Let go of me, you monster!

19:26.684 --> 19:29.751
Ow! Stan, you're kicking my face!

19:33.643 --> 19:35.224
Oh! We're safe.

19:35.226 --> 19:36.291
He can't get past the...

19:46.770 --> 19:49.472
Look what I did!

19:50.908 --> 19:52.174
Where the hell have <i>you</i> been?

19:52.176 --> 19:53.575
I almost went down there.

19:53.577 --> 19:56.045
Family! Oh, sweet family!

19:56.047 --> 19:58.447
I want you to know that
I haven't forgotten you,

19:58.449 --> 19:59.915
even if I came close.

19:59.917 --> 20:03.919
I'm here now, and I want to do
what you want to do.

20:03.921 --> 20:06.655
I want to raise this child.

20:06.657 --> 20:08.799
- Daddy's here.
- I'm not doing that anymore.

20:08.892 --> 20:09.954
Thank God.

20:22.339 --> 20:23.672
Poor bastard.

20:23.674 --> 20:25.941
Feels good to have
things back to normal.

20:25.943 --> 20:27.542
- Stan?
- Whaddup?

20:27.544 --> 20:32.281
Have you heard the new hi-fi's
with quadraphonic sound?

20:32.283 --> 20:34.083
They're the best hi-fi's for...

20:34.085 --> 20:36.351
- Ja-a-a-zz.
- Ja-a-a-zz.

20:36.353 --> 20:39.020
No. No! No!

20:39.022 --> 20:40.890
No-o-o-o!

20:40.892 --> 20:43.759
<i>That's right! "American Dad!"
is now a show that exists</i>

20:43.761 --> 20:49.164
<i>on TV in the basement of the family of
"American Dad!"</i>

20:49.166 --> 20:50.900
Another great episode.

20:50.902 --> 20:53.702
So long, nighthawks.

20:56.640 --> 20:58.374
Bye! Have a beautiful time!

